features: ANTI-COLIC BABY BOTTLE. Anti-Colic internal vent system is clinically proven to reduce colic. Decreases spit-up, burping and gas.
CONSISTENT FLOW RATE. Vacuum-free feeding is closest to breastfeeding and Dr. Brown’s silicone nipples provide a consistent flow so babies can feed at their own pace.
PRESERVES NUTRIENTS. The anti-colic vent system is proven to help preserve bottle milk nutrients and aids in digestion for a better night’s sleep.
BREASTFEEDING BOTTLE. The breast-like nipple shape encourages a proper latch for a more natural bottle feeding experience and eases the transition from breast to bottle and back again.

BOTTLE GROWS WITH BABY. Dr. Brown’s Natural Flow Anti-Colic Options+ baby bottle works best with the internal vent system in place but can be removed as baby’s feeding develops – no need to introduce a different bottle.
SUSTAINABLE BABY BOTTLE. Dr. Brown’s Wide-Neck bottle is designed to nourish through all of baby’s feeding stages and is recyclable.

PLASTIC BANK COLLABORATION. Dr. Brown’s has collaborated with Plastic Bank to prevent ocean plastic and reduce their plastic footprint. Purchasing Dr. Brown’s baby bottles help toward their commitment to prevent 31 million plastic bottles from entering the ocean annually. Learn more at PlasticBank.com.
DISHWASHER SAFE. Safe for use in dishwasher (top rack only), electric and microwave sterilizers or boiling water. BPA Free. 5 oz/150 mL, Level 1 Nipple, 4-Pack, 0m+
body.description: Your options have never been better with Dr. Brown’s Natural Flow® Anti-Colic Options+™ Wide-Neck Baby Bottle. The anti-colic internal vent system is clinically proven to reduce colic. Dr. Brown’s® bottles provide a more comfortable feeding experience for baby by decreasing spit-up, burping and gas. This vacuum-free feeding is closest to breastfeeding and Dr. Brown’s® silicone nipples provide a consistent flow so baby can feed at their own pace. The breast-like nipple shape encourages a proper latch for a more natural bottle feeding experience and eases the transition from breast to bottle and back again. Dr. Brown’s vent system is proven to help preserve bottle milk nutrients and aids in digestion for a better night’s sleep. The silicone nipple, together with the internal vent system, offer a reliable and trusted bottle feeding experience that makes Dr. Brown’s the #1 Pediatrician Recommended Baby Bottle in the U.S.* Made to grow with baby, our bottle is designed to nourish through all of baby’s feeding stages and is recyclable. Safe for use in dishwasher (top rack only), electric and microwave sterilizers or boiling water. BPA Free.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best bottles we’ve tried
reviews.reviewText: We’ve used this bottles for about 6 months now and they’re the only thing that helped with my daughters gas. She would take just about any bottle, but this one was easier on her tummy. We have had a couple of them leak, but it’s always been user error. I wouldn’t trust the reviews complaining of leaking, especially if your bottle is just upside down. There is probably a better way to store your bottle. They come with caps to insert inside to prevent leakage while traveling. It’s super simple. We’ve also had no issues of melting. It’s honestly a little concerning that some of these reviewers are taking care of babies but can’t properly use a baby bottle. Anyways.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Baby love it.
reviews.reviewText: Love this bottle. The spacious opening eases formula scooping, streamlining the feeding process. Its ample size suits my growing baby's hearty appetite. The bottle's durability and easy cleaning further enhance its appeal, making it a reliable companion in our daily routine.The easy grip design ensures a secure hold for both parents and the growing baby. This thoughtful feature anticipates the future stages of independence, making it a user-friendly choice as our little one transitions to self-feeding.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Love these bottles. They’re made from high quality plastic and have very minimal leakage issues. Perfect for my 4 month baby

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Our go to brand
reviews.reviewText: Only bottles I've found that don't create a vacuum. I used the narrows for our first child but our 2nd couldn't take them with his tongue tie. Thank goodness for the wide neck! We tried 2 other brands before settling on this and it works great! I love they're moving away from the blue vents too so we can use it with or without in the green option

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My favorite baby bottles
reviews.reviewText: I haven't tried other bottles, I haven't had the need because I love Dr Browns bottles…. I have twins and it has helped me a lot with the issue of colic,they are going to be 3 months old and for the first time I have not had even a colic crisis lasting more than two hours in them. The nipple has excellent quality, there’s no milk drawing, the only difficult thing is when it comes to washing them because they have 2 additional pieces but at least for me that is not a problem. I'm going to buy the 9 ounce ones soon.If you want good bottles and avoid excess colic in your baby, this is your best option.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Our daughter's go-to bottles
reviews.reviewText: One aspect I appreciate about Dr. Brown's nipples is the range of flow options available. As my baby grew, I could easily switch between slow, medium, and fast flows, ensuring a comfortable feeding experience at every stage. One downside is that the extra parts, including the vent insert and tube, require thorough cleaning, adding a step to the washing routine. Another downside is that sometimes it leaks, even when you screw everything together tightly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Adecuados para lactancia mixta
reviews.reviewText: Los amo, mi bebé los usa desde que nació y no ha habido confusión para el entre el pecho y el tetero ya que tenemos lactancia mixta.
Ayudo mucho a reducir los cólicos de mi bebé, es un poco complicado el lavarlos, lleva un poco de tiempo pero cumple con la función
No son originales ,su empaque deja mucho q desear y el plástico se ve amarillo a diferencia de uno original

I love these bottles, really hard to find so have to order online. Disappointed that the LARGE bottles come with a size 1 nipple but I love not worrying about missing the scoop of formula because it has a large opening. Do not use straw part when using bottle warmer, it will leak everywhere.

reviews.reviewTitle: Seems ok but the quality is iffy
reviews.reviewText: Received the four bottles and 3 seem ok but 1 leaks. We didn't know what caused the leak and thought it was all the bottles. But then I decided to methodologically use and observe each bottle and finally figured out that only one was leaking. Try figuring that out when a hungry baby is crying. Not fun.Anyway, really weird and to be honest I am disappointed at the quality. Unlikely to purchase again.
These worked well as long as you do not fill it above the indicated line and you tightly close the bottle.
